{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Odd saturation\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Two waveshping saturation styles using sin() functions, feturing {\i odd harmonics}. *Wavy Top, no discontinueties but may fold the wavefom over a bit at some settings. *Flat Top, waveform flatens off at 0dB. Can be used to add vibe or as a maximiser.\par}
}

{\rtf1\ansi\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0 \fswiss Helvetica;}{\f1 Courier;}}
{\colortbl;\red255\green0\blue0;\red0\green0\blue255;}
\widowctrl\hyphauto

{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs36 Smooth Clipper\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Waveshaper that gets much more distorted near -1dB, but never reaches a perfectly flat top. Hard clipper at the output to prevent levels over 0dB. Can be used to add vibe or as a maximiser.\par}
}

